subject: Re: [junit] HELP , Which web-link is available to free download Junit E-book?
msgSnippet: May I suggest that a visit to the documentation section of the JUnit website would be an excellent first stop? http://junit.sourceforge.net/#Documentation
messageBody:
May I suggest that a visit to the documentation section of the JUnit
website would be an excellent first stop?

http://junit.sourceforge.net/#Documentation

There is also an excellent list of articles:

http://www.junit.org/news/article/index.htm

As well as a list of dead tree reading material:

http://www.junit.org/news/book/index.htm

Hope this helps. I learned more from articles than books when I
started learning JUnit, so I feel confident in feeling that this
advice will help you.

Simon
